<Layout
  title="Pocket Door Installation Cost in Florida: What to Expect (2025)"
  description="How much does pocket door installation cost in Florida? Learn about pricing factors, average costs, and how to budget for your pocket door project in Orlando, Miami & Fort Myers."
  keywords="pocket door installation cost, pocket door cost Florida, pocket door price Orlando, pocket door installation Miami, pocket door Fort Myers cost"
>

  <article class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <header class="mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-2">
          <a href="/blog" class="text-accent hover:underline">Blog</a> &mdash; January 15, 2025
        </p>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-wide text-primary mb-4">Pocket Door Installation Cost in Florida: What to Expect (2025)</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-500">A comprehensive guide to budgeting for your pocket door project in Orlando, Miami, and Fort Myers.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-gray-600 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p>
          If you are considering adding a pocket door to your home or office in Florida, understanding the costs involved is an important first step. Pocket doors are a practical and stylish solution for saving space, and the investment pays off in both functionality and property value. At <a href="/" class="text-accent hover:underline">Pocket Door Services</a>, we help homeowners and businesses across the state make informed decisions.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Average Pocket Door Installation Costs</h2>
        <p>
          In Florida, the average cost for a standard pocket door installation ranges from $500 to $2,500. This includes the door, hardware kit, and labor. A basic hollow-core pocket door with standard hardware falls on the lower end, while solid-core doors with premium tracks and soft-close mechanisms push the price higher. For commercial projects, costs can be higher depending on fire rating requirements and door dimensions. Learn more about our <a href="/service/commercial-door-installation" class="text-accent hover:underline">commercial door installation</a> services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Factors That Affect Pricing</h2>
        <p>
          Several factors influence the total cost of a pocket door installation. Wall modifications are the biggest variable — installing a pocket door in an existing wall requires cutting into the framing and may involve rerouting electrical wiring or plumbing. New construction installations are generally less expensive because the wall cavity is built from scratch. Door material, size, hardware quality, and finish also play a role.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Conversion vs. New Installation</h2>
        <p>
          Converting a standard swinging door to a pocket door is one of the most popular projects we handle. Conversions typically cost between $1,000 and $3,000 because they require wall framing modifications. A fresh installation during new construction or a renovation where walls are already open is less labor-intensive, keeping costs closer to the $500 to $1,500 range. Our <a href="/service/roller-replacement-and-frame-repair" class="text-accent hover:underline">roller replacement and frame repair</a> services address common issues after installation.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Getting the Best Value</h2>
        <p>
          To get the best value, always request multiple estimates and ask about warranty coverage. At Pocket Door Services, we provide transparent pricing with no hidden fees. Our technicians serving <a href="/location/pocket-door-services-orlando" class="text-accent hover:underline">Orlando</a>, <a href="/location/pocket-door-services-miami" class="text-accent hover:underline">Miami</a>, and <a href="/location/fort-myers" class="text-accent hover:underline">Fort Myers</a> carry years of experience in residential and commercial installations.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Ready to Get Started?</h2>
        <p>
          Whether you are building new or retrofitting, our team can help you choose the right pocket door solution within your budget. <a href="/contact" class="text-accent hover:underline">Contact us for a free estimate</a> or call <a href="tel:9547275410" class="text-accent hover:underline">(954) 727-5410</a> to discuss your project today. We also offer <a href="/service/lock-repair" class="text-accent hover:underline">lock repair</a> and <a href="/service/hinge-repair-replacement" class="text-accent hover:underline">hinge repair services</a> for existing doors.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
